 <div class="container Product">
        <div class="row my-5">
            <div class="col-12 d-flex align-items-center mb-5 unset">
                <div class="img w-50 text-center animate__animated animate__fadeInLeft">
                    <%= image_tag 'roastery', class:"pic Product_row_col-12_img_pic"%>
                </div>
                <div class="info w-50 animate__animated animate__fadeInRight">
                    <h2 class="name text-orange font-italic">Euro Espresso Coffee</h2>
                    <h2 class="price text-secondary font-italic"><%=@product.price%></h2>
                    <p class="description text-secondary">
                        <%= @product.description%>
                    </p>
                    <%= form_with model: OrderProduct.new, remote: true do |f|%>
                        <%= f.hidden_field :product_id, value: @product.id %>
                        <%= f.number_field :quantity, in: 1..20, step: 1, :class => "text-orange text-center p-2 font-italic"%>
                        <%= f.submit "ADD TO CART", class: "btn btn-outline-orange py-2 rounded-0 font-italic ml-3"%>
                    <% end %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container Comment">
        <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h1 class="m-0 text-orange font-italic text-center animate__animated animate__fadeInDown">
                    REVIEWS
                </h1>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12 mt-2 border-b-orange animate__animated animate__fadeInLeft">
                <div class="w-75 mb-3">
                    <h6 class="text-orange font-italic">Anonymous</h6>
                    <p class="text-secondary">
                        Arrived last night... I could not WAIT to cup this coffee up and give it a taste this morning!
                        So i
                        made an overnight cold brew for my partner! We had our wishes this morning... but were somewhat
                        let
                        down. Brightness and fruitiness are both quite underwhelming. The coffee is roasted "dry" ie.,
                        marginally dark but with no lacquering and unfortunately produces a final, cupped or
                        cold-brewed,
                        product that has a definite "green" aftertaste. NOT at all satisfying... it's ok... definitely
                        not
                        great.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="w-75 mb-3">
                    <h6 class="text-orange font-italic">Abdurahman</h6>
                    <p class="text-secondary">
                        I love the taste of Kenya Peaberry its great bean
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="w-75 mb-3">
                    <h6 class="text-orange font-italic">Hollybelle</h6>
                    <p class="text-secondary">
                        This is one of the most sophisticated dark roast flavours from Peets I have ever enjoyed. It is
                        not nearly as dominant as Aged Sumatra, nor heavy as a French Roast but combines a delightful
                        smell with a very smooth satisfying flavour to one of the best select roasts in Peet repertoire
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12 py-4 border-b-orange animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
                <h6 class="text-orange font-italic mb-3">My review for Euro Espresso Coffee</h6>
                <form class="w-50">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <textarea class="form-control rounded-0 bg-none text-light" placeholder="Your comment" rows="5"></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-orange rounded-0 font-italic">SUBMIT</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

